Virtual Machine resources define the computing capabilities and configuration of a VM.

Key resources include:

* CPU (processing power)
* Memory (RAM)
* Storage (disks)
* Networking (connectivity)

For example, a high-performance application requires more CPU and RAM.

A real-life use case is selecting appropriate resources for a database server requiring high memory.

Another example is lightweight applications running on smaller VM configurations to reduce cost.

Understanding VM resources is crucial for performance optimization and cost efficiency.
